---
description: Unit testing rules and conventions
globs: tests/*.py
---
- Use `pytest` exclusively as the testing framework.
- Maximize edge-case coverage, specifically targeting regex boundary conditions and malformed AST nodes in parser modules.
- Implement `pytest.mark.parametrize` for data-driven test execution.
- Strictly isolate tests: mock all filesystem interactions, I/O operations, and external Logseq dependencies using `unittest.mock` or `pytest-mock`.
- Ensure all tests are deterministic and do not leak state.